### Methods in C#

A method is a block of code that performs a specific task. Methods help organize code, reduce repetition, and improve readability.

### Method Syntax

```csharp
[accessModifier] [returnType] MethodName([parameters])
{
    // Method body
    return value;  // If not void
}
```

### Basic Example

```csharp
static void Greet(string name)
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Hello, {name}!");
}

static int Add(int a, int b)
{
    return a + b;
}
```

### Calling Methods

```csharp
Greet("Alice");          // Call void method
int sum = Add(5, 3);     // Call method with return value
Console.WriteLine(sum);  // 8
```

### Method Components

| Part | Description | Example |
|------|-------------|---------|
| Access modifier | Visibility of the method | `public`, `private`, `static` |
| Return type | What the method returns | `int`, `string`, `void` |
| Method name | Identifier for the method | `CalculateTotal` |
| Parameters | Input values | `(int x, int y)` |
| Body | Code to execute | `{ return x + y; }` |

### Return Types

```csharp
// Returns nothing
static void PrintMessage(string msg)
{
    Console.WriteLine(msg);
}

// Returns a value
static int Square(int x)
{
    return x * x;
}

// Returns multiple values (tuple)
static (int, int) GetMinMax(int[] numbers)
{
    return (numbers.Min(), numbers.Max());
}
```

### Expression-Bodied Methods (C# 6+)

```csharp
static int Add(int a, int b) => a + b;
static void Print(string msg) => Console.WriteLine(msg);
static bool IsEven(int n) => n % 2 == 0;
```

### Local Functions (C# 7+)

Methods inside methods:

```csharp
static int Calculate(int x, int y)
{
    return Multiply(x, y) + Add(x, y);

    int Multiply(int a, int b) => a * b;
    int Add(int a, int b) => a + b;
}
```

### Method Overloading

Same method name with different parameters:

```csharp
static int Sum(int a, int b) => a + b;
static int Sum(int a, int b, int c) => a + b + c;
static double Sum(double a, double b) => a + b;
```

> **Key Point:** Methods should perform a single, well-defined task. Use camelCase for method parameters and PascalCase for method names. Methods with `void` return type do not require a `return` statement.

### Default Parameters

```csharp
static void Log(string message, string level = "INFO")
{
    Console.WriteLine($"[{level}] {message}");
}

Log("Starting");           // [INFO] Starting
Log("Error!", "ERROR");    // [ERROR] Error!

